{"page":1,"prev_page_endpoint":null,"next_page_endpoint":null,"total_pages":1,"reasons":[{"created_at":"2013-11-16T05:07:11Z","content":"Our custodians are the first line of defense against infectious diseases. When MRSA became an issue a few years ago, the vigilance of our custodians kept it from spreading. When other schools have closed unexpectedly as their populations were laid low by the flu, MSAD #28 schools have remained open each flu season. The health of our buildings and our students is too important to be in the hands of anyone except our professional, trained, and dedicated custodial staff.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Kathleen Bower","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69397897"},{"created_at":"2013-11-21T03:40:19Z","content":"We already know the custodians we have are safe with our students.  They are invested, caring custodians looking out for the best interests of the students in this school.  They also know who is supposed to be in the school after hours using our facilities.  They also care about the staff working here at our school and look after them also and are always willing to lend a hand to help them above and beyond the call of duty.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Melissa Willley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/70164837"},{"created_at":"2013-11-15T23:53:48Z","content":"I work in this school and see the great benefit of continuing the contracts of our excellent custodial staff.  They are dedicated to their jobs and our students.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Catherine Courand","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69356618"},{"created_at":"2013-11-16T21:48:13Z","content":"Our custodians care about the students and go the extra mile for all of us.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Maryann Callen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69511659"},{"created_at":"2013-12-03T14:38:56Z","content":"The outsourcing proposal neglects the fact that the first person at CRES most students and parents encounter is the proud, smiling guy who waves to them at drop-off.  You cannot pay a contract staffer to smile or care for our kids. But that stuff has value. And it can't be replaced once you eliminate the full-time positions.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Richard Thackeray","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/71909931"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T10:44:59Z","content":"I grew up in the area and would like to see it remain as safe as possible. Keeping the people in place that have an interest in the school and kids would help do that.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Patti  Buchanan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/286679"},{"created_at":"2013-10-21T11:49:01Z","content":"CRMS strives to provide a caring and consistent community for students.  Our custodial staff does more than provide a clean, safe environment for students at the school.  They interact with kids, participate in events such as teacher-student basketball, and work with teachers to provide the best learning environment possible for students.  I do not support outsourcing custodial staff.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rebecca Graham","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66073474"},{"created_at":"2013-12-11T16:18:22Z","content":"The custodians of our school are worth our community's continued commitment.  They are worth every penny they are paid.","like_count":0,"author_name":"James Cook","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/145442"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T10:59:08Z","content":"The staff does a great job, and they are as much a part of the the life of the schools as the teachers are.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Fran  Hodgkins","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/875426"},{"created_at":"2013-10-22T22:50:50Z","content":"Our Custodians are a local and important part of our school community!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shannon Orestis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66255983"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T00:06:38Z","content":"Though I live in Union my son lives in the MSAD district. Employees of the schools are much more likely to put a lot of care into their work and towards our kids.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jim  Doble","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9960241"},{"created_at":"2013-11-15T23:50:14Z","content":"Keep it local.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Eric Martin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69356371"},{"created_at":"2013-10-22T23:06:12Z","content":"Our custodians do a great job. They know our school and have a vested interest in keeping it going.","like_count":0,"author_name":"erma colvin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66260444"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T22:23:44Z","content":"The staff does so much more than could possibly be on a job description and are amzing with our students.","like_count":0,"author_name":"judy laurence","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66389711"},{"created_at":"2013-12-02T23:36:58Z","content":"I work at a school in MSAD 28.  I'm concerned with the safety of students, staff, personal and school property if  we outsource custodial services.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cynthia Archambault","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/49432405"},{"created_at":"2013-12-02T16:33:53Z","content":"I personally know how important these people are to our students.  They keep our kids safe as well as keep their school clean.  They also keep our kids smiling because they care about them and their school community.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Constance Pound","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/71779847"},{"created_at":"2013-10-24T01:46:25Z","content":"This staff has helped us countless times in so many ways!!! Say NO to outsourcing!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Robbin Charkowick","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66405277"},{"created_at":"2013-10-20T13:04:43Z","content":"The custodians at CRMS are an integral part of our community.  They are not only invaluable founts of information and deeply tied to the concerns of the students and staff, but they are friends who lend support and encouragement to students and staff every day.  They show interest in school events and sports, they play on the staff basketball team during spirit week, they fundraise with us during Movember, they bring treats and uplifting conversation to tired teachers working late hours, they write editorials in local newspapers discussing school issues and they provide a million other unseen services to the school that would be lost if we let the school outsource. This is a misguided attempt to reduce costs that would replace very special, local staff, with an impersonal, for-profit company that is unconnected to our community or concerns.  Please stop outsourcing!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ruth Poland","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66003223"},{"created_at":"2013-10-21T11:06:16Z","content":"As a teacher, I value and trust our custodial staff.  I KNOW them and can rely on them.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Patricia Friesland","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66070581"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T22:19:44Z","content":"I want to keep the custodians who care about our children, buildings and community! These people are part of our families and do an excellent job which you want have by outsourcing to save a few bucks.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Leroy Philbrook","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66389362"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T22:30:21Z","content":"These are friends and coworkers who make the school a friendly, clean and safe place for our kids. We need them in our building.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ian McKenzie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66390288"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T16:19:59Z","content":"I do not support making the numbers look good in the short term over the long term best interest of our community and it's children. I know that the school board has to make a budget work but I suspect there is a better way than this to control costs. Every member of our school district staff plays a role in the great job our schools have done and need to continue to do.","like_count":0,"author_name":"David Orsmond","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66348752"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T15:07:48Z","content":"I detest people losing their jobs for a corporation's benefit.  Let these people work for the schools!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sally Russillo","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66340753"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T13:26:31Z","content":"Custodians are a vital part of the school community.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Erin Lourie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11197069"},{"created_at":"2013-12-02T05:35:48Z","content":"As a teacher in MSAD#28 I value the investment our custodial staff have not only in caring for our facilities but also caring for our students and staff. Because they are a part of the community they take a personal interest in supporting and nurturing children and in the safety and well being of students and staff. they are there on a moments notice when a child is sick in our room or supplies run out or there is a facilities need but also if a child is lost, hurt or just needs an adult friend. Contracted custodians will not have the same presence or involvement in our school community. In this day of threatened school security I value the presence and awareness of our school custodians.","like_count":0,"author_name":"maureen gordon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/71723001"},{"created_at":"2013-11-25T13:30:13Z","content":"I support our local custodians and all the hard work, dedication and loyalty they give us. Shouldn't we do the same for them? Thank you for your hard work in keeping our schools in pristine conditions!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sherrie Lake","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52241767"},{"created_at":"2013-10-21T21:56:53Z","content":"This is important to me because I am a teacher in the district. I have witnessed what the custodial staff does for us every single day. They go above and beyond their duties, and are important to the success of our students and staff. The custodians are a large factor in creating and maintaining our positive school community.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kisha Marsh","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66133469"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T16:42:09Z","content":"Safety of the students.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Vicki Worden","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66351194"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T12:09:58Z","content":"The custodial staff is the backbone of the school. Though our children have new teachers every year, these familiar faces keep them safe and comfortable throughout their school careers. They deserve our support!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kathleen Meil","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66321576"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T13:22:20Z","content":"Our custodial staff at CRES goes above and beyond what is on their to do list.  They are as invested in our children as every other staff member there is.  They do not just show up and clean the building and go home.  They greet our children when they arrive, making sure with the arrival of the first bus that the lights are properly working to slow down cars.  They are there to help out in the cafe at lunch and they are there all day long to help out when needed.  They know each of our children by name.  They know the parents and who belongs in the building as well as who belongs with what student.  They help set up for afterschool activities and lend a helping hand without ever asking how much more time is this going to add to my day.  They do this with a smile and always have a smile.  They are a part of this school community and would be a great loss.  You can not replace this group of individuals.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tammy Morris","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66329351"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T00:10:10Z","content":"Our CRMS custodians mean more to us than the job they do at our school.  Some are volunteers with our Cross Country team, take part in our activities along with the rest of our staff, they welcome us to school each day, and wish us a good evening when we leave.  They are part of our CRMS community.  A community that involves our teachers, our support staff, our kitchen ladies, our bus drivers, our maintenance staff, our administration, our nursing staff and secretaries, but most importantly of all, they are part of our CRMS family.  They fight the war on germs for us, they keep us safe inside and outside our school building, they create an environment we want to work in, and our students want to learn in.  \r\nTo outsource the service these people provide every day is wrong on many levels.  I DO NOT  support this decision to outsource custodial services.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ellen Curtis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66268516"},{"created_at":"2013-10-21T13:57:23Z","content":"Our school would not be the same without the caring members of our janitorial staff. We know and respect them and they provide positive role models for our students. No outsourcing!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kathy Foss","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66082985"},{"created_at":"2013-10-24T00:56:09Z","content":"In just one \"typical\" day our custodians: Act as crossing guards, clean up vomit, assist with lunch duty, repair broken entry doors, coordinate contractors working in the building, deliver tissues and copy paper to those who ask, unclog toilets, AND welcome children by name, help kids find their items in lost and found, serve as volunteer coaches, cover breaks for secretaries, hang artwork and turn kilns on and off overnight, and basically, do anything asked of them with willingness and a smile.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Andrea Pierce","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66401517"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T22:26:39Z","content":"It is my mother's job, and I wouldn't want her to be without one.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lacy Massengale","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66389955"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T01:07:35Z","content":"They do so much for our kids and our school. They have always lended a hand when asked. They ALL go above and beyond. They care about the school and the kids.","like_count":0,"author_name":"beth chamberlin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66273445"},{"created_at":"2013-10-22T19:29:06Z","content":"I have seen how much more they do for our students than clean.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Constance Pound","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66209361"},{"created_at":"2013-10-24T15:40:23Z","content":"These people deserve to keep their jobs and my kids and I deserve to know and trust all the school staff.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Byrnes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66464587"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T01:52:04Z","content":"I have watched these good people help kids safely cross the street since my son was in Mrs. Milliken's kindergarten class.  They do all sorts of good works for the school community, far more than just being \"custodians\".  They are invested in the school community and truly care about the kids.  This is apparent every single day - day in, day out, year in, year out.  Good people, all, who have more than earned the right to remain a solid part of the school community.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Deb Whittier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66277258"},{"created_at":"2013-10-23T23:40:44Z","content":"This staff does an incredible job of making sure that the entire building is safe and student-ready.  We need to maintain workers who are invested in our community.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michelle Gabrielsen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66395813"},{"created_at":"2013-10-30T01:16:35Z","content":"So I do not have to find them new jobs and feed them .","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stanley Polchinski","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66941333"},{"created_at":"2013-10-24T11:51:37Z","content":"The custodians know the people of the schools like no outsourced contractors could.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jane Babbitt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/50887048"},{"created_at":"2013-10-22T10:35:41Z","content":"The custodial staff is part of our team to make MSAD 28 schools the best place for our students to learn.  As an art teacher,  the custodians turn up my kiln  at night,  move displays boards around school,  install permanent art collections and tiles on walls...the list could go on!  They go way beyond their job description daily!\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nKristen Andersen","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kristen Andersen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12073258"}]}
